5:
That's the long and short of it. 
As for me, I'm taking a little break.
8:
Nao, on the other hand, is hard at
work. Last I saw her, she was all fired
up about finding a brand-new world.
10:
Nova's doing better as well—I even
saw him smiling the other day.
That's all thanks to Sho, I'd wager.
13:
Nimbus... Well, he's still Nimbus.
Spends his days partying and
drinking himself silly.
16:
...I might need to get Claw to have
an intervention at some point.
21:
Oh, right. I also heard from Mr.
Takamori that they're going to hold
a graduation ceremony.
24:
It'll be a joint one, for middle and
high school students. I guess I'll be
taking part too, alongside Sho and
Yuki. Better late than never.
27:
So... No pressure or anything, but if
you keep lying around here, you're
gonna end up missing your son's
big moment.
32:
*sigh* It's still all so surreal. I have so
many things to talk to you about. So
many questions to ask...
35:
I feel like I'm back to being a little kid
again.
38:
Anyway. I'll come by again soon.
Till next time.
47:
Ayumu! Come on man, you're hella
late.
51: Sorry! I just had a lot to talk about.
55:
Oh, right. Hey, we can do this some
other time too, you know. If you
wanna keep talking to them, that's
cool—
59:
Nah, it's okay. Let's do it now. Rip the
bandage off real fast.
61:
God knows why I even agreed to go
"pick up girls" with you in the first
place. I'm going to regret this...
65:
No backing out now! Besides, we're
doing this for Nova, remember?
H-hey, wait up!
75:
Shota's here to see you, Ayumu... 
Get out of bed!
89:
What... is this place? Are we in a
hospital? It's... surprisingly nice.
94:
You know... I swear, I had the
strangest dream.
99:
Hm? Come to think of it, so did I.
Don't tell me...
106: Ayumu was some kind of hero?
112: Haha, what are the chances of that?
122:
Wow... There's crashing and burning,
and then there's THAT. What a
horrible day...
126:
I seriously hope nobody saw ANY of
that... How embarrassing...
139:
I'm... your friendly neighborhood
curry chef! ...In training.
142:
I heard someone crying and had to
see what was up... And then I found
you! What are you doing here?
147: Say... That cat isn't yours, is it?
152:
Let me guess. Parents got mad at
you because you wanted to keep it?
155:
M-Mama got mad, and said she
hates cats! B-but I...
157:
I screamed at 'er and ran away! And
ran and ran and... *sniffle* Now, I
dunno where my house is!
165:
No worries! We'll get you home safe
and sound.
167:
Make sure to have a proper talk with
your mom when you get back,
okay? Tell her just how much you
want to keep this cat.
173:
Hey, if you can't keep it, maybe
someone else can? We can think of
some other ideas together.
176:
Where there's a will, there's a way.
You'll see.
181: Come on, then. I'll bet you're starving!
184:
Sometimes I wonder why I was born.
If there was any meaning to it. And
to be honest, I haven't found an
answer.
185:
But what I do know is that I've
changed—and grown. All the people
that I've met have made me
stronger.
186:
If I can use that strength to help
someone out there—someone who's
struggling and unsure, just like I
was...
188:
Well, that would fill my life with
meaning. 
It would make me happy.
193: Where are you right now, I wonder?
194:
Far away, shivering in the cold dark,
all by your lonesome?
195:
I hope that someone out there finds
you—and that they lend you their
strength.
196:
I hope the warmth they show you is
enough to spur you on... To help you
get up, and take just one more step
forward.
197:
So, if you feel the same... If you want
to keep going, and you see an
outstretched hand offering to help
you...
199:
Reach out. Grab it.
And never let go.
201:
Then one day, when you come
across a new, untrodden road, you'll
have the courage to walk
it—alongside your friends, just like I
once did.
